HT|n|at|^B"The advantages of opening a weak two are:|
HT|o|at|^C(1) limiting the hand immediately; |PG||
HT|n|at|^B"The advantages of opening a weak two are:|
HT|o|at|^C(1) limiting the hand immediately;| 
HT|p|AT|^C(2) directing the opening lead;|PG|| 
HT|n|at|^B"The advantages of opening a weak two are:|
HT|o|at|^C(1) limiting the hand immediately;| 
HT|p|AT|^C(2) directing the opening lead;| 
HT|q|AT|^C(3) taking away bidding space from the opponents."^*N|PG||


CP|1|at|
^b@2^Z@3MM: |CP||AT|That is fine. But the opponents get the same information and can use it against you.|PG|| 
