ST||sk|n|MD|1SAKT532H4DJT65C56,,s96ha532d974qcq97,|sv|o|rh||AH|Hand E2|mb|2sp?|lb|*bWhat should North bid?^^p|cp|8|AT|^B@2^Z@3Kiamemnon: ^*N|cp||at|North evaluates the hand in view of information gleaned from the 2@S bid before selecting his/her bid. South does not have an opener and is suggesting that spades should be trumps. Therefore, responder should not be interested in a game contract unless responder has more than an opening hand. Responder usually should accept the Weak Two bid, unless there is clearly a better spot.|PG||NT|^B@2
