There are two reasons for jumping to game over partner's Weak Two Bid. One is because you expect to make the contract. The second, Preemptive, is because you expect that the opponents can make a contract, and that whatever penalty your side suffers is likely to be less than the value of the opponents' contract.|PG||NT|^B@2
South has to lose at least one heart trick, one diamond trick and two club tricks. South may have to lose two heart tricks if the @HA is unfavorably placed.|PG||NT|^B@2
Although you cannot make 4@S, what can the opponents make—4@H or more. The opponents can probably take at least 11 tricks in a heart contract. They have at most one spade loser—since they have only three spades between them. |PG||NT|^B@2
