st||pn|Movie Maker,Silent Opponent, Howard, Silent Opponent|sk|s|md|3hk43,,,|rh||ah|Board G2|ah|Ogust by Howard|sv|n|MB|2hp?|lb|*bWhat would be your bid Movie Maker?^^3h|MB|3H|cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If you have 3-card support and at least 4 points, you should raise to 3 at least. Again, this is based on the Law of Total Tricks (you have 9 trumps, so you are safe bidding a 9 trick contract). Below I will discuss when you should think about bidding 4, but I want to emphasize that, if your partner opens a Weak Two and you have 3-card support, you must at a minimum bid 3 regardless of your point count. Bridge experts call this "furthering the preempt" and it is a very effective tactic.|PG||NT||
